2.8 2.9 2.10 2.11 2.12 2.13 2.14 2.15 3.1 3.2 3.3 3.4 3.5 3.6 3.7 3.8 3.9 3.10 3.11 3.12
Arrives at work alert, well-groomed, and dressed appropriately for the job.
Maintains a productive, flexible, and hard-working approach to work.
Asks appropriate questions when unsure of a policy or procedure.
Displays an honest and ethical approach to work.
Offers to help whenever possible or appropriate.
Works hard to become excellent at doing tasks to set a positive example for others.
Works willingly and cooperatively with people from a variety of ethnic, social, or educational backgrounds.
Helps others learn needed knowledge and skills.
Standard 3: Successful Customer Relations Speaks clearly and courteously on the telephone to customers, coworkers, supervisors, and professionals.
Arranges a dining area for a specified type of service (table service, buffet, banquet, cafeteria, etc.) and for specified seating requirements.
Sets a table with linen, flatware, glassware, and condiments in accordance with several types of service.
Presents all menu items correctly plated and garnished.
Greets and seats guests properly.
Takes guests' orders accurately.
Demonstrates knowledge of menu items and is able to describe them to guests.
Is able to answer guests' questions about menu items.
Serves a guest meal efficiently, including serving and removing food and beverage items.
Processes and presents a guest sales check properly.
Clears guests' tables properly.
Writes a simple business letter with assistance to a customer or professional using appropriate language style and format.
Standard 4: Kitchen Basics Reads instructions, recipes, menus, and policies quickly and with comprehension.
Weighs and measures food and other resources accurately.
Converts weights and measures accurately.
Stocks and replenishes food, beverages, condiments, and sundries at side/server stations.
Uses, handles, and cleans mixing equipment using correct procedures.
Uses, handles, and cleans cooking equipment using correct procedures.
Uses, handles, and cleans dishwashing equipment using correct procedures.
Uses, handles, and cleans waste-disposal equipment using correct procedures.
Standard 5: Food Preparation and Storage Demonstrates preparing and storing sandwiches.
Demonstrates basic egg cooking, including frying, scrambling, poaching, or basting.
Demonstrates breakfast cooking, including pancakes, waffles, bacon, sausages, breads, potatoes, or hot cereals.
Demonstrates preparing and storing fruits and vegetables.
Demonstrates proper garnishing to enhance texture, color, and appearance of foods.
Demonstrates preparing and storing salads and dressings.
Demonstrates preparing and storing rice, pasta, and other cooked grains.
Demonstrates preparing and storing cakes, cookies, and pies.
Demonstrates preparing and storing puddings, custards, mousse, soufflÃ©, or other dessert items.
Demonstrates preparing and storing cooked fish, shellfish, meats, and poultry.
Demonstrates preparing and storing brown, white, or preprepared stock.
Demonstrates preparing and storing soups and sauces.
