Standard 5: E valuate effective conflict prevention and management techniques.
Determine the origin and development of attitudes and behaviors regarding conflict.
Determine how similarities and differences among people affect conflict prevention and management.
Implement strategies that prevent or resolve conflict.
Assess community resources, services, and agencies that support conflict prevention and management.
Standard 6: Demonstrate teamwork and leadership skills in the family, workplace, and community.
Describe and demonstrate collaborative group leadership (in which group members: develop a common vision; relate and cooperate with each other to achieve that vision; and assume shared responsibility for each other, the group, and the larger community).
Create an environment that encourages and respects the ideas, perspectives, and contributions of all group members.
Demonstrate strategies to motivate, encourage, and involve group members, utilizing their strengths and limitations.
Demonstrate techniques that develop team and community spirit, including integrating new team members.
Standard 7: Demonstrate standards that guide behavior in interpersonal relationships.
Examine types of standards for making judgments and the role these standards play in guiding interpersonal relationships.
Assess the nature of issues and situations in view of personal standards.
Apply standards when making judgments or taking personal actions.
Demonstrate ethical behavior in family, workplace, and community.
Examine the relative merits of opposing points of view regarding current ethical issues.
