Standard 4: Demonstrate ability to acquire, handle, prepare, and serve foods to meet nutritional and wellness needs of individuals and families across the life span.
Apply USDA Dietary Guidelines, including the Food Guide Pyramid, in planning to meet nutrition and wellness needs.
Investigate food modifications made for nutritional challenges such as vegetarianism, sports nutrition, diabetes, lactose intolerance, and food allergies.
Demonstrate ability to select, store, prepare, and serve nutritious, safe, and aesthetically pleasing foods.
Assess practices individuals and families can use to conserve and recycle resources related to nutrition and wellness.
Demonstrate ability to select, use, and maintain food preparation and storage equipment.
Evaluate recipes for nutritional value and preparation processes.
Apply resource management principles when planning, purchasing, preparing, and serving food.
Standard 5: Analyze factors that affect food safety and sanitation from production through consumption.
Determine conditions and practices that promote safe food handling.
Analyze safety and sanitation practices throughout the food chain.
Analyze federal, state, and local inspection and labeling systems that protect the health of individuals and the public.
Monitor food borne illness as a health issue for individuals and families.
Standard 6: Analyze impacts of science and technology on nutrition and wellness.
Explain impacts of technological advances on selection, availability, preparation, and home storage of food.
Identify effects of food science and technology on meeting nutritional needs.
Examine scientific and technological impacts on the availability, selection, use, and storage of wellness-related equipment and products.
Standard 7: Identify career paths related to nutrition and wellness.
Identify opportunities for employment and entrepreneurial endeavors related to nutrition and wellness.
Summarize roles and functions of individuals engaged in careers related to nutrition and wellness.
Describe education and training requirements and opportunities for a variety of career paths related to nutrition and wellness.
