4.1 4.2 4.3 4.4
5.1 5.2 5.3 5.4 5.5 5.6
Standard 4: Develop basic skills and personal qualities needed for success in family, community, and workplace settings.
Demonstrate responsibility, teamwork, and integrity.
Apply reading, writing, mathematics, listening, and speaking skills in family and workplace settings.
Demonstrate respect for multiple diversities with sensitivity to anti-bias and equity in gender, age, race, culture, ethnicity, socioeconomic status, and exceptionalities.
Demonstrate the ability to transfer basic skills and personal qualities to family, work, and community settings.
Standard 5: Demonstrate management of personal resources to become independent, contributing, and responsible students, employees, and family members.
Examine needs, wants, principles, goals, and economic resources and their relationship to personal resource management.
Create systems and strategies for managing personal activities and resources such as schedules, assignments, school materials, and projects.
Set goals for wellness practices to maximize present and future health, appearance, and peak performance.
Utilize management skills and services to reach personal goals.
Determine and assume responsibility for maintaining personal appearance appropriate for specific settings.
Determine and demonstrate time management strategies to achieve personal goals.
