4.1 4.2 4.3 4.4 4.5 4.6 4.7
5.1 5.2 5.3
Standard 4: Evaluate properties of textiles and fashion products to determine performance in a variety of end uses.
Select appropriate terminology for identifying, comparing, and analyzing the most common generic textiles fibers and their performance characteristics.
Assess effects of textiles characteristics on design, construction, care, use, and maintenance of products.
Evaluate the use of textiles and fashion technologies for interior furnishings and products.
Analyze the impact of science and technology on textiles and fashion.
Explore current technology and trends that facilitate design and production of textiles products and apparel.
Select appropriate procedures for care of textiles products.
Utilize a variety of presentation media such as photography, video, and software to demonstrate and evaluate textile and fashion products.
Standard 5: Demonstrate skills needed to produce, alter, or repair textiles products and apparel.
Demonstrate apparel and textile design skills selection and use of fabric, texture, line, pattern, and color for producing textile and fashion products.
Use a variety of equipment, tools, and supplies for apparel and textiles construction alteration, and repair.
Demonstrate basic skills for producing, altering, and repairing textile products and apparel.
Standard 6: Examine potential career paths in textile and fashion industries to determine knowledge, skills, attitudes, educational preparation, and employment opportunities associated with each.
